caption: Now, I try and visit at least one every few weeks. The bartenders are so friendly and funny, and they always give great service, while making wonderful drinks. Usually when I am here, it is late night and they have pizza by the slice for sale. Their pizza is FIRE. Even if youre not in here late night, I definitely recommend trying it.

Not good.  Stopped through here while Downtown for work since it was one of the only places open at the time within walking distance. Had OK reviews so tried it. It was pretty expensive for just a pizza, figured it had to be good. Nah, just below average at best. Typical bland pizza crust, just tastes like sandwich bread. Sauce was pretty bland. Just seemed like a filler just to call it a pizza. Cheese was alright, PJ's and Dominos has better flavor.  For the price, it should be a little better with premium ingredients. This just tasted like an average froze pizza.

Awesome gesture though! We got the stuffed portabella hand tossed 12". More than enough for 2 people.

Some friends and I are going to Pearl Street for a surprise bday party tonight and I personally like to know where the food I eat is sourced from. I called to ask where they receive their dairy products and the girl responded very put out “now’s not a good time, we’re in the middle of lunch, call back tomorrow” and I then let her know we were dining there tonight, where she said to call back in an hour. If it weren’t for plans we have already made for the birthday girl, then we would not still be going here after that response. All customers are important, even the ones who call in on the phone. Not great customer service, to be told to call back the next day and have your question brushed off. I understand lunch rush can be crazy and trying to answer a question you may not personally know the answer to can be a hassle finding a knowledgeable resource, but the way this was handled was very unprofessional and rude to a new customer who cares about where her food comes from and what’s in it.

Really disappointing experience. Wish I could comment on the food, but never made it that far. After a concert, we were looking for a place to grab some late night food. The reviews were great and we were hungry. We had 2 minors in tow and searched everywhere on the page and reviews as many places do not allow minors after a certain time. Before we walked in, we noticed the door said “All ages welcome”, so we figured we were ok. We entered, sat down, and waited for menus. About 5 minutes later, a woman came up to us and said they had run out of pizza and their cook had walked out on them. She laughed unapologetically and then told us they also don’t serve minors so they wouldn’t be able to stay. When I questioned the door, she responded, “Oh that’s not really what it means. We don’t allow minors after like 11 or something.” I would have loved to try the pizza and had a great experience, but was left with a disappointing time.

Atmosphere was great for a Monday evening.  There was a concert in town, so the place was hopping!  The service was prompt and friendly, and we were heading to the concert, so we just had a pizza on the fly.  It was an average pizza, and the toppings were plentiful!  All in all, the place is kind of quaint, the beer menu is full of local choices, and the menu is fairly standard.

Probably 1 of my Top 3 Fav places to Eat pizza and honestly has great atmosphere and. Very kind staff. Gone there 3 times in last month. Dont pass it up  parking is a bare at moments but its downtown peopleg..

Very disappointing range of options for vegetarians, vegans, gluten free and other allergies. Came here for a family dinner but won’t be coming here again until that changes.  Please consider making more options for crusts, etc to cater to these groups. ( no need for egg in crust!) Hate to give such a low review but I also hate when the only thing on the menu I can eat is iceberg lettuce and olive oil.... Veganism is a growing movement and it would be awesome if you made some more menu options that catered to customers who don’t eat animal byproducts for ethical, environmental and health reasons.

The service was good I have not been problem the food was good as well I didn't think their sauce had much for spices in it clear sauce could have been a little better than that

Went here for lunch on a Sunday.  Really neat atmosphere. Server was very polite. Ordered a meat lovers pizza. It came out and was cooked perfectly.  Lots of toppings, wasnt greasy, and the crust had a light crisp. It was all very good except for the crust flavor, because there was none. It tasted like crispy cardboard. Everyone in my party felt the same. We devoured the pizza, but no one ate the crust. Maybe if they would drizzle some melted garlic butter and parmesan cheese on the crust after it came out of the oven, that would give it some flavor. Overall, neat little place with an awesome atmosphere. Next time we will try something other than pizza.
